vant 1095–avant 1138":"before 1095–before 1138","1075–1136":"1075–1136","1075–1150":"1075–1150","1095–1138":"1095–1138","1090–1127":"1090–1127","1115–1179":"1115–1179","1126–1176":"1126–1176","1050–1122":"1050–1122","1048–1119":"1048–1119","1090":"1090","avant 1095":"before 1095","avant 1122":"before 1122","1176":"1176","1075":"1075","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1127":"1127","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1136":"1136","1179":"1179","1122":"1122","avant 1138":"before 1138","28 January 1119":"28 January 1119","environ 1127":"about 1127","1119":"1119","Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgique":"Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgium","Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgium":"Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgium","Ath, Hainaut, Belgique":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgium","Liessies, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Liessies, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"D'ATH","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Arati, Meenakshi, Raj, Binod, Kalyani, Manoj, Narayan, Padmaja, Pramod, Rajesh, Satya, Sita.","English: variant of   Ash   with fused Old French preposition <i>d(e)</i> ‘of, from’, a topographic name for someone who lived near an ash tree, or a habitational name from a place called with the Old English word <i>æsc</i>, such as Ash in Derbyshire, Devon, Dorset, Herefordshire, Kent, Shropshire, Somerset, and Surrey, and Ashe in Devon and Hampshire. Compare   Nash  .","English: nickname perhaps from Middle English <i>dasch(e)</i>, <i>dassh(e)</i>, <i>daish</i> ‘violent or sharp blow’."],"variants":[{"name":"Ash","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>asche</i> ‘ash tree’ (Old English <i>æsc</i>), hence a topographic name for someone living by an ash tree or a habitational name from any of the many places in southern and central England named with this word (Derbyshire, Dorset, Hampshire, Herefordshire, Kent, Surrey, Shropshire, Somerset, and elsewhere).","Americanized form of German   Asch   and   Esch  , the latter ultimately also of Swiss German origin (see   Oesch  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , with the same meaning as 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Ada","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin; it was not in general use before the late 18th century. It may be a Latinate variant of the biblical name   Adah .  However, it has also been explained as a pet form of   Adele   and   Adelaide  , Germanic female names of which the first element is <i>adal</i> ‘noble’. It was borne by a 7th-century abbess of Saint-Julien-des-Prés at Le Mans."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ada D'ATH was born before 1095, in Ath, Hainaut, Belgium, her father, Gauthier d'Ath, was 44 and her mother, Ada de Ramerupt, was 46. She had at least 2 daughters with Guy Widon DE CHIEVRES. She died before 1138, in Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgium."},"et":{"avant 1095–avant 1138":"enne 1095–enne 1138","1075–1136":"1075–1136","1075–1150":"1075–1150","1095–1138":"1095–1138","1090–1127":"1090–1127","1115–1179":"1115–1179","1126–1176":"1126–1176","1050–1122":"1050–1122","1048–1119":"1048–1119","1090":"1090","avant 1095":"enne 1095","avant 1122":"enne 1122","1176":"1176","1075":"1075","1095":"1095","1150":"1150","1050":"1050","1127":"1127","1138":"1138","1115":"1115","1126":"1126","1048":"1048","1136":"1136","1179":"1179","1122":"1122","avant 1138":"enne 1138","28 January 1119":"28. jaanuar 1119","environ 1127":"umbes 1127","1119":"1119","Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgique":"Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgia","Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgium":"Chièvres, Hainaut, Belgia","Ath, Hainaut, Belgique":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgia","Liessies, Nord, No